lang=ZH-CN>听到了，掐断</span>A<span lang=ZH-CN>和</span>B<span lang=ZH-CN>的联系，开始装作是</span>B<span
lang=ZH-CN>来回复给</span>A<span lang=ZH-CN>。如果</span></span><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Apple Color Emoji";mso-ascii-font-family:
FangSong;mso-fareast-font-family:FangSong;mso-hansi-font-family:FangSong;
mso-bidi-font-family:SimSun;mso-char-type:symbol-ext;mso-symbol-font-family:
"Apple Color Emoji"'>&#128025;</span><span lang=ZH-CN style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:FangSong;mso-bidi-font-family:SimSun'>给出的回复总是“</span><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:FangSong;mso-bidi-font-family:SimSun'>that<span
lang=ZH-CN>’</span>s scary<span lang=ZH-CN>”又或者 “</span>oh, I don<span
lang=ZH-CN>’</span>t know<span lang=ZH-CN>”。这样看起来并无事实错误的回复，总归容易让</span>A<span
lang=ZH-CN>引起怀疑。因为此类问题中，</span>A<span lang=ZH-CN>需要的是提供建议，解决问题的答案。而且这样不能给出实质建议的回复，可以靠语言形式</span>(form)<span
